import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    data.groupby('Year').count()['Entity'].plot(kind='line', ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the trend of natural disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.bar(data['Entity'], data['Deaths'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which type of natural disaster has caused the most deaths?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Deaths'])
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Deaths'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Deaths')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by natural disasters?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('Year')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.bar(data['Year'], data['Deaths'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which year had the highest number of deaths caused by natural disasters?')
    plt.axvline(x=data.iloc[0]['Year'], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data.iloc[0]['Deaths']:.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
